<p itemprop="description">A lead service designer leads the service design function across the organisation, setting strategic direction for service transformation and ensuring user-centred service design principles are embedded throughout all government services. They manage service design teams and drive organisational service excellence.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define and implement service design strategy across the entire organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead and manage service design teams and service transformation programmes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish service design governance, standards, and operating models</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Champion user-centred service approaches at executive and policy level</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build strategic partnerships with service design and transformation communities</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Oversee service design capability development and organisational change</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation in service design methodologies and transformation approaches</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Ensure service excellence and user focus across all organisational programmes</li>
    </ul>
</section>

